net.sf.mmm.util.query.api.path

Interface EntityAlias<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the generic type of the type of this EntityAlias.
    All Superinterfaces:
    AttributeReadName, PathFactory, PathRoot<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Alias

    public interface EntityAlias<E>
extends PathRoot<E>
    This is the interface for an EntityAlias used in an SQL statement e.g. inside a a FROM block.

      • getEntityType

        Class<?> getEntityType()
        Returns:
        the optional Class reflecting the internal entity of the source. It is not bound to <E> as the internal entity does not necessarily have to be the queried result type. May be null.
